I"ÿ<p>The fundamental relation</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">dE = TdS - PdV</script>

<p>tells us that</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">T = \frac{\partial E}{\partial S}\bigg|_V,\qquad -P = \frac{\partial E}{\partial V}\bigg|_S.</script>

<p>other content here</p>

<p>Sometimes however, we are interested in calculating quantities such as</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">\frac{\partial E}{\partial T}\bigg_V.</script>

<p>Can we come up with a Maxwell relation that helps with this? Consider the Legendre trasnformed quantity $F = E - TS$. Thus,</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">dF = -SdT - PdV,</script>

<p>which tells us that</p>

<script type="math/tex; mode=display">-S = \frac{\partial F}{\partial T}\bigg|_V</script>

